@scene feature_showcase
title: The Feature Showcase
subtitle: DendryNexus Mechanics Demo
new-page: true

Welcome to the **Feature Showcase**. Each path below demonstrates a different DendryNexus engine feature.

[? if reputation >= 5 : *Your reputation precedes you — some paths are easier now.* ?]

[? if silver <= 2 : *Your purse is light. The merchants eye you warily.* ?]

Your current stats — Wit: **[+ wit +]**, Courage: **[+ courage +]**, Silver: **[+ silver +]**, Reputation: **[+ reputation +]**

- @priority_demo: Priority & Frequency (Card Draw Order)
- @tag_demo_hand: Tag-Based Choices (Deck Built from Tags)
- @goto_demo: Conditional Go-To (Branching Paths)
- @gotoref_demo: Go-To-Ref (Dynamic Navigation)
- @setroot_demo: Set-Root (Default Continue)
- @call_demo: Call (Run Another Scene's Actions)
- @conditional_text_demo: Conditional Text Rendering
- @unavailable_demo: Unavailable Subtitle
- @difficulty_curve_demo: Custom Difficulty Curves
- @main_hall: Return to the Hall

@scene priority_demo
title: Priority & Frequency Demo
subtitle: Card Draw Order
is-hand: true
max-cards: 3

This hand has a deck with **priority** and **frequency** settings. Draw cards and notice:

1. **Priority 3** cards (Urgent) are drawn first
2. **Priority 2** cards (Important) come next
3. **Priority 1** cards (Normal) fill remaining slots
4. Among same-priority cards, **frequency** controls the weighting

- @priority_deck: Draw from the Priority Deck
- @main_hall: Return to the Hall
- @feature_showcase: Back to Showcase

@scene priority_deck
title: Priority Deck
is-deck: true

- @priority_card_urgent: Urgent Message
- @priority_card_important_1: Important Notice A
- @priority_card_important_2: Important Notice B
- @priority_card_normal_rare: Rare Event
- @priority_card_normal_common: Common Event

@scene priority_card_urgent
title: Urgent Message
subtitle: Priority 3 — Drawn First
is-card: true
priority: 3
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: reputation = reputation + 1

This card has **priority: 3** — the highest in the deck. It is always drawn before any lower-priority cards. With **max-visits: 1**, it disappears after being played once.

This is how DendryNexus ensures introductory or story-critical cards appear before random content.

Reputation: **[+ reputation +]**

- @priority_demo: Return to hand

@scene priority_card_important_1
title: Important Notice A
subtitle: Priority 2
is-card: true
priority: 2

This card has **priority: 2**. It will be drawn after all priority-3 cards are exhausted, but before priority-1 cards.

- @priority_demo: Return to hand

@scene priority_card_important_2
title: Important Notice B
subtitle: Priority 2
is-card: true
priority: 2

Another **priority: 2** card. When multiple cards share the same priority, the engine uses **frequency** to weight which one is drawn.

- @priority_demo: Return to hand

@scene priority_card_normal_rare
title: Rare Event
subtitle: Priority 1, Frequency 20
is-card: true
priority: 1
frequency: 20

This card has **frequency: 20** (default is 100). Lower frequency means it's *more likely* to be chosen among same-priority candidates — it effectively has higher draw weight.

- @priority_demo: Return to hand

@scene priority_card_normal_common
title: Common Event
subtitle: Priority 1, Frequency 200
is-card: true
priority: 1
frequency: 200

This card has **frequency: 200** (double the default). Higher frequency means it's *less likely* to be chosen — lower draw weight relative to other priority-1 cards.

- @priority_demo: Return to hand

@scene tag_demo_hand
title: Tag-Based Choices
subtitle: Deck Built from Tags
is-hand: true
max-cards: 4

This hand has a deck that uses **tag-based choices** instead of listing individual scene IDs. The deck contains all scenes tagged with `tavern_event`.

- @tag_deck: Draw from the Tavern Events Deck
- @feature_showcase: Back to Showcase

@scene tag_deck
title: Tavern Events
subtitle: Cards Tagged tavern_event
is-deck: true

This deck uses `#tavern_event` — it automatically includes every scene in the game with the tag `tavern_event`. Add new cards just by tagging them.

- #tavern_event: Tavern Event

@scene tavern_bard
title: A Bard Performs
is-card: true
tags: tavern_event
on-arrival: wit = wit + 1

A travelling bard plays a haunting melody. You learn a new turn of phrase.

This card is included in the Tavern Events deck because it has `tags: tavern_event`. It was not listed by ID — the `#tavern_event` syntax pulled it in automatically.

Wit: **[+ wit +]**

- @tag_demo_hand: Return to hand

@scene tavern_fight
title: A Fight Breaks Out
is-card: true
tags: tavern_event
on-arrival: courage = courage + 1

Two farmers argue over a goat. You step in and separate them before anyone draws steel.

Tagged with `tavern_event` — automatically included in the tag-based deck.

Courage: **[+ courage +]**

